Input: Suppose we have the following objective function: $\argmin_{w}  rac{1}{2} 
orm{Xw-y}^2_2 +  rac{1}{2}\gamma 
orm{w}^2_2$ What is the gradient of $ rac{1}{2} 
orm{Xw-y}^2_2 +  rac{1}{2}\lambda 
orm{w}^2_2$ with respect to $w$? Choices: a) $\nabla_w f(w) = (X^\top X + \lambda I)w - X^\top y + \lambda w$ b) $\nabla_w f(w) = X^\top X w - X^\top y + \lambda$ c) $\nabla_w f(w) = X^\top X w - X^\top y + \lambda w$ d) $\nabla_w f(w) = X^\top X w - X^\top y + (\lambda+1) w$ 
Output: {'sol': 'a'}
